subSubSection.paragraph:
Coloration. —Generally body and appendages generally transparent, covered with tiny orange-red bars and bands; cornea black, eyestalk transparent; pereiopods II (chelipeds) covered with particularly broad orange-red band along all segments (
Fig. 5 a, b
).
